				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$x(t) = a + (b + c) \cdot t$$\end{document}where x is the input energy over time (t), a is the initial construction energy including the embodied energy within the construction materials, b is the energy consumed in operation over a period of time t, and c accounts for the maintenance for a given time period. The output is described by the following function:8y(t)=d·t\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$y(t) = d \cdot t$$\end{document}where d is the output from the plant. The EPT is reached using Method 1 when:9y(t)=x(T)\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
