The EPT using Method 2 shows that a given plant reaches an EROI of 1 when the energy expenditures are in chronological order. The difference between this method and the previous method is that the total energy used for operation and maintenance is not summed and included with plant construction but is considered to be ongoing throughout the lifetime of the plant (Atlason and Unnthorsson 2014b). The EPT using real-time energy use can be expected to differ slightly from the EPT using lifetime energy use. Using Method 2, the EPT is reached when:10y(t)=x(t)\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
